-- Blackstone, Gulf investors buy minority stake in UAE's GEMS Education
-- By Nadia Saleem
-- Wed Oct 15, 2014 05:45AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Oct 15 (Reuters) - Dubai's Fajr Capital said on Wednesday that it was part of a group including Blackstone <BX.N> and Bahrain sovereign fund Mumtalakat that acquired a "significant minority stake" in United Arab Emirates-based GEMS Education.

No price for the deal was given in the statement posted on Fajr's website, which said Blackstone had made its investment through its Tactical Opportunities fund.